Syrup Trailer (2013) -  Amber Heard: An unofficial trailer has been released for the adaptation Syrup, directed by Aram Rappaport and starring Amber Heard and Shiloh Fernandez. Author/screenwriter Max Barry posted the video to his YouTube channel, in response to a low-resolution version that recently leaked. Shiloh Fernandez stars as Scat, an unemployed college graduate who has a million-dollar idea the he tries to protect from the conniving love of his life, 6 (Amber Heard). Take a look at the trailer, along with a message from Max Barry.

Syrup comes to theaters in 2013 and stars Amber Heard, Brittany Snow, Kellan Lutz, Shiloh Fernandez, Greg Paul, Toby Hemingway, Natalie Gal, Rachel Dratch. The film is directed by Aram Rappaport.

Cast: Amber Heard, Brittany Snow, Kellan Lutz, Shiloh Fernandez, Greg Paul, Toby Hemingway, Natalie Gal, Rachel Dratch
